<br>
The following things I was not able to do before the above patch. Maybe it was just me, but I have played BST, MAG, and NEC and have not been able to have the below happen previously.<br>
<br>
/pet report health -- you will get an update from anywhere in the zone. I left my pet parked by a Coterie camp in Tenebrous Mountains and went to the Katta zone. Just before I summoned it to me, for a test, I hit my health hot key. Boom, got an answer.<br>
<br>
/pet guard here -- The pet hears it accross the zone. As a test, I summoned a new pet at the Katta zone to Tenebrous Mountains. I did not park him here, instead I headed off to the bank downsatirs. As usual, the pet went into it's &quot;OMG, I lost my master for a second&quot; despawn/respawn routine. You know the one, he gets stuck and disappears but, respawns at his last zone-in/creation point and attempts to get to you again. Rinse and repeat forever. I hit my guard here hot key and went upstairs. Sure enough, he was parked half way between the zone and the top of the ramp down to the bank area. I had received no confirmation text from him though.<br>
<br>
/pet back off -- Same range situation. I got hit by a mob way off from where my pet was parked while I was pulling. I hit back off hot key immediately. Pet didn't charge off after the mob when it got close to him. Again no text from pet at that distance.<br>
<br>
/pet {all I have tried} -- It appears the time period you must wait before the pet will &quot;hear&quot; your next command attempt has been shortened. When I park my pet on Luclin hill sides I will have it follow and guard multiple times until it gets to just the right spot and stops &quot;sliding.&quot; [those who have tried this know what I am doing re. the irritating pet slide problem - ya I know, only a visual issue, but still is frustrating] It was irritating how long I had to wait between commands. Now I can almost hit the guard command instantly after the follow. Back off is also much faster between successfull attempts. Report health is almost as fast as I can hit the key (within reason - lol). I sure hope VI doesn't &quot;fix&quot; this.....<br>
<br>
----- The short version -----<br>
<br>
It appears our pets receive the commands from a long distance, but when they reply in &quot;/say&quot; text you dont receive it and do if it is a reply such as health status. Timer between multiple commands seems to be shorter.<br>
